The '''''Encyclopedia of Indo-European Culture''''' (abbreviation: ''EIEC'') is an [[encyclopedia]] of [[Indo-European studies]] and the [[Proto-Indo-Europeans]]. The encyclopedia was edited by [[J. P. Mallory]] and [[Douglas Q. Adams]] and published in 1997 by [[Fitzroy Dearborn]]. Archaeological articles are written by Mallory, linguistic articles are written by Adams, and includes a distinguished ''Who's Who'' of 1990s Indo-Europeanists who made contributions as sub-editors. While not a [[polemic]], the work in part responds to [[Colin Renfrew, Baron Renfrew of Kaimsthorn|Colin Renfrew's]] [[Anatolian hypothesis]] of [[Proto-Indo-European Urheimat hypotheses|Indo-European origins]].

